Source: libgbm
Section: non-free/x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Eugene Nuribekov <eugene.nuribekov@toradex.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>=11~)
Standards-Version: 4.1.4
Homepage: http://nxp.com

Package: libgbm-vivante1
Section: libs
Architecture: arm64
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libgal-vivante1 (=6.2.4.p4.0-1), libdrm-vivante1, libwayland-server0, libc6
Provides: libgbm1 (=18.3.6-2)
Description: generic buffer management API -- runtime
 This package contains the GBM buffer management library.  It provides a
 mechanism for allocating buffers for graphics rendering tied to Mesa.
 .
 GBM is intended to be used as a native platform for EGL on drm or openwfd.

Package: libgbm-vivante1-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: libgbm-vivante1 (=6.2.4.p4.0-1) 
Multi-Arch: same
Description: generic buffer management API -- development files
 This package contains the GBM buffer management library.  It provides a
 mechanism for allocating buffers for graphics rendering tied to Mesa.
 .
 GBM is intended to be used as a native platform for EGL on drm or openwfd.
 .
 This package provides the development environment for compiling programs
 against the GBM library.

